    {
      "id": "a19a1536f2eb2e1bd59c210daeb018e25aa43c9d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 116,
        "name": "Brian J. Murrell",
        "email": "brian.murrell@intel.com",
        "username": "brian",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-01-16 12:56:05.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nDespite the build showing a passing result, there are lots of untrapped error situations in the build log such as:\n\n../build/lbuild: line 288: autodetect_distro: command not found\n\n../build/lbuild: line 302: autodetect_target: command not found\n\n../build/lbuild: line 382: push_exit_trap: command not found\n\n../build/lbuild: line 571: fatal: command not found\n\n../build/lbuild: line 579: /var/lib/jenkins/workspace/lustre-reviews/arch/x86_64/build_type/server/distro/el6/ib_stack/ofa/BUILD/lustre/lustre/kernel_patches/targets/.target: No such file or directory\n\n+ fatal 1 'Config file for target  missing from /var/lib/jenkins/workspace/lustre-reviews/arch/x86_64/build_type/server/distro/el6/ib_stack/ofa/BUILD/lustre/lustre/kernel_patches/kernel_configs/.'\n../build/lbuild: line 633: fatal: command not found\n\n+ fatal 1 'No available target archs to build.'\n../build/lbuild: line 242: fatal: command not found\n\n../build/lbuild: line 1993: ../build/lbuild.old_school: No such file or directory\n\n../build/lbuild: line 1995: old_school_download_kernel: command not found\n\nLots of places where the build should have actually failed if the fatal() function were not missing, etc.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "632d9790fe943ff06e9c8040b6d774b7788d3577",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 109,
        "name": "Christopher J. Morrone",
        "email": "morrone2@llnl.gov",
        "username": "morrone"
      },
      "date": "2013-01-16 18:24:05.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nWhat is the build system doing?  What is \"lbuild.old_school\"???",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "5b9a3a2fa0e9392fd8efa3bb4a65ec6503f8ead9",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 116,
        "name": "Brian J. Murrell",
        "email": "brian.murrell@intel.com",
        "username": "brian",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-01-16 20:12:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nlbuild.old_school looks like leftovers that should have been removed in changeset 9aa2968b965a5acdf127a5635dfde8950bc8d3a2.\n\nThis changeset would be as good as any to finally remove that.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "33089c22341bf505bb94b245c84ad687d2a97e3d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 109,
        "name": "Christopher J. Morrone",
        "email": "morrone2@llnl.gov",
        "username": "morrone"
      },
      "date": "2013-01-16 21:07:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nBrian, no, that file WAS removed from Lustre.  It already does not exist on the master branch.\n\nBut something in your build farm is looking for it anyway.  I can't fix this, because the problem is in the build farm scripts.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "95ec73cbe6783b8aad1403254a1d36856af28642",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
        "name": "Maloo",
        "email": "maloo@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2013-01-17 05:12:02.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nTests received by maloo, run on el6/x86_64: (https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/66ef5d26-6064-11e2-ba32-52540035b04c).  Ran 1 tests.  1 tests failed: node-provisioning-1.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "a6d5d3da70d9c563a5b2da912866a9c58b60386c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 116,
        "name": "Brian J. Murrell",
